    "# 🧭 Cross-Absolute Selection Principle (CASP)\n",
    "## Comprehensive Theoretical and Computational Framework\n",
    "\n",
    "### Overview\n",
    "This notebook provides a rigorous formalization and computational simulation of the **Cross-Absolute Selection Principle (CASP)**, a groundbreaking theoretical construct in advanced mathematical ontology.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theoretical Foundation\n",
    "The CASP emerges from the **Enhanced Mathematical Ontology of Absolute Nothingness**, offering a sophisticated framework to:\n",
    "- Minimize cross-absolute interaction action\n",
    "- Maximize informational consistency across transfinite mediation spaces\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "## 🔷 Fundamental CASP Postulates\n",
    "\n",
    "### Postulate I: Minimal Interaction Action\n",
    "$$ \\mathcal{A}_{\\text{min}} = \\arg \\min_{M \\in \\mathcal{M}} \\| S_1 M S_2^T \\|_F $$\n",
    "\n",
    "### Postulate II: Entropic Compatibility\n",
    "$$ \\Delta \\epsilon = |\\epsilon_1 - \\mathrm{Tr}(I I^T)| < \\delta_\\text{tolerance} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "### Postulate III: Directional Coherence Maximization\n",
    "$$ \\max \\left( \\langle S_1 M, S_2 \\rangle \\right) $$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Notation:**\n",
    "- $I$: Information tensor\n",
    "- $M$: Mediator matrix\n",
    "- $S_i$: Signature matrices of absolute entities"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "16d3c9e9",
   "metadata": {},
